<H3> <TI>   Gold Reserves, Production Figures Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gold Reserves, Production Figures Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806161594 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
0400 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia intends to increase its gold production 
substantially in the very near future, says Yevgeniy Bychkov, 
the head of Russia's Committee for Precious Metals and Precious 
Stones. This year the country has increased gold production from 
149.5 to 157 tons. Gold reserves currently amount to 307 tons. 
Of this total 157.2 tons are held by the Committee for Precious 
Metals. The rest is under the jurisdiction of the Central Bank. 

</TEXT>

