<H3> <TI>   Caucasian Public, Cossacks Demand Ingush Hostage Release </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Caucasian Public, Cossacks Demand Ingush Hostage Release </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806131494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1244 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806131494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 8 TASS -- The forum of public 
organisations of the people of northern Caucasus and Cossack 
troops from Russia's south is prepared to take tough and 
efficient measures if six Ingush hostages earlier detained in 
North Ossetia are not released until June 10. 
  An appeal to the North Ossetian president, which came to 
ITAR-TASS from the Ingush permanent mission in Russia today, 
says that if the hostages are held any longer, the forum of 
public organisations reserves the right to hold up traffic from 
North Ossetia to the territories of the Stavropol, Kuban and the 
Don region as of June 11. Other protest actions and sanctions 
will be taken in future, the appeal said. 
  Representatives of the north Caucasian people and Cossack 
troops from Russia's south come out for strict implementation of 
the Russian president's decree of May 30, 1994, including in 
part concerning the immediate release of hostages, the appeal 
said. 

</TEXT>

