<H3> <TI>   Sakha Republic Introduces New Rules for Foreign Visitors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sakha Republic Introduces New Rules for Foreign Visitors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0906110994 Moscow Russian Television and Dubl Networks in 
Russian 0600 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW0906110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television and Dubl Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report; from the "Dalniy Vostok" program] </F>
  [Text] The edict issued by Mikhail Nikolayev, president of 
the Sakha Republic, Yakutia, establishes special rules for entry 
into the republic. They concern citizens of foreign states and 
CIS countries, as well as those republics of the Russian 
Federation which have not signed the federal agreement. To 
enter Yakutia from now on, it is necessary for them to have 
special invitations approved by the local authorities. In a 
number of instances, citizens in given categories could be 
refused permission to enter the republic of Sakha, or be 
expelled before the expiration of their stay. The grounds for 
this specifically are actions which go against the interests of 
state security or public order, established traditions and 
standards of moral behavior, as well as breaches of customs, 
currency, and other laws of the Russian Federation and Yakutia. 

</TEXT>

