<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Government Structure in Komi Republic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Government Structure in Komi Republic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906082994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2154 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Makarov] </F>
  [Text] Syktyvkar, 9 Jun -- The Komi Government resigned en 
masse on Tuesday [7 June] as Yuriy Spiridonov has taken up the 
post of head of the Republic of Komi, which, under the new 
Constitution, is also head of the government. He will have five 
deputies and it is thought there will be 17 ministries, as well 
as the administration of the head of the Republic of Komi, 
working as a single body ensuring the operation of the 
government he heads. 
  At a session of the republic's Supreme Soviet, Spiridonov 
warned that in his government the number of civil servants would 
be cut back considerably, although the professionals would 
remain on the job. 
  A special parliament resolution passed on Wednesday made 
provision for appropriations for the material-technological and 
financial working of the head of the Republic of Komi, setting 
the salary for the post at 50 times the minimum monthly salary 
set by Russian legislation. 

</TEXT>

