<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko Calls Policy Unclear </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko Calls Policy Unclear </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906095794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government has no clear budget policy today, 
while the draft budget it has submitted is simply a statement of 
expenses, Federation Council chairman Vladimir Shumeyko told 
journalists today. He believes the draft budget has no purpose. 
Shumeyko compared it to porridge spread thinly on a plate. 
Answering a question about the Federation Council's proposal to 
increase military expenditure, Shumeyko said that this is a 
demand put forward by life itself. 

</TEXT>

