<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Choice Backs More Defense Spending </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Choice Backs More Defense Spending </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806112694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1020 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] This morning the Russia's Choice faction in the 
State Duma decided to back the draft federal budget in the 
second reading if 3.5 trillion rubles more are allotted for the 
needs of defense structures, Russia's Choice member Sergey 
Yushenkov told Interfax. 
  He stressed that as the Chairman of the State Duma Committee 
on Defense he thought that the Army must be given 55 trillion 
rubles instead of the 37 trillion rubles stated in the draft 
budget. Yushenkov said he would vote for the proposal of the 
parliamentary Budget Committee providing for the increase in the 
funds for defense needs by 3.5 trillion rubles and for the 
amendment put forward by the Committee on Defense demanding that 
18 trillion rubles more be allotted for these purposes. 

</TEXT>

