<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Supports Security Council Ban on Weapons to Yemen </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Supports Security Council Ban on Weapons to Yemen </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806203594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1400 
GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Yuriy Kozlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 8 Jun -- Russia favors the unconditional 
observation of the provisions of the UN Security Council 
resolution of 1 June this year on banning weapons' supplies to 
Yemen. The ITAR-TASS correspondent was told this today by 
Grigoriy Karasin, director of the Russian Foreign Ministry's 
department of information and the press. He said that it was in 
the common interests of the world community "to deprive the 
internecine conflict of fuel." The warring sides, he said, 
should finally heed the voice of reason, cease the senseless 
destruction of their own country, and return to the path of 
political dialogue. 
  Despite the efforts to stop the bloodshed, the official 
spokesman of the Russian foreign policy department said, reports 
are continuing to come from Yemen about large-scale combat 
actions and more deaths and destruction. In this connection, he 
stressed, Russia welcomes the efforts to achieve a normalization 
of the situation by the UN Security Council, the League of Arab 
States, the countries of the Persian Gulf, and other 
international mediators, and Russia confirms its readiness to 
coordinate actions toward the soonest possible cessation of the 
fratricidal conflict. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

