<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Guards Fire Warning Shots at Poachers Off Kurils </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Guards Fire Warning Shots at Poachers Off Kurils </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806210894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1805 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Poachers tried to enter the Russian waters off the 
isle of Kunashir in the Russian Far East on 14 occasions from 
June 1 to 6. They approached from the Japanese island of 
Hokkaido without identification signs or navigation lights in 
poor visibility. 
  The Russian border guards had to fire warning shots, 
Lieutenant General Vitaliy Sedykh, commander of the Pacific 
border guard district told the Japanese consul in Vladivostok 
Wednesday. 
  The Russian border guard press office reported that the 
poachers did not respond to all demands to stop. As they 
escaped, they cut off the nets in which large amounts of fish 
died. 
  Sedykh said that warning shots were fired in the early hours 
of June 4 and 6 when two poaching schooners and six schooners 
respectively were sighted. 
  The border guards fired over 300 30 mm and around 10 76 mm 
shells. 

</TEXT>

