<H3> <TI>   Tajik Leader Vows Punishment for Killers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tajik Leader Vows Punishment for Killers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0806124394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 8 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM0806124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Anatoliy Stasovskiy report: "Tajikistan Fights Terror"] </F>
  [Text] On 7 June Colonel General Andrey Nikolayev, 
commander in chief of Russian Federation Border Troops, received 
from Tajikistan a telegram from Imamali Rakhmonov, chairman of 
the republic's National Assembly. In it the head of Tajikistan 
expressed his sincere condolences in connection with the tragic 
deaths of Russian border guards -- Lieutenant Colonels 
Borisenkov and Leontikov. "The criminals," the telegram says, 
"who have encroached on a most blessed thing -- the lives of 
Russia's sons who, answering the call of duty and conscience, 
were protecting the Tajik soil that had become their own -- will 
not go unpunished. Some of them are already in the hands of the 
law, the others will be found and punished with all the severity 
of the law...." 
  Meanwhile, in Tajikistan everything is being done to get 
control of the acute criminogenic situation. On 7 June 24-hour 
joint patrols of Tajik and Russian servicemen began. Areas 
where Russian servicemen and their families live have been put 
under special guard. 

</TEXT>

