<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Prime Minister Arrives; Agreements To Be Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese Prime Minister Arrives; Agreements To Be Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806140494 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1150 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806140494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no date as received] -- The prime minister of 
the Socialist Republic of Vietnam arrived in Ukraine today on an 
official visit. 
  UNIAN has learned from sources close to the Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs that the following documents will be signed 
during the visit: a consular convention, an agreement on 
cooperation in the sphere of culture, education, and science, 
and an agreement on protection of investments. A treaty on 
friendship and cooperation between the two countries will be 
initialled. 
  Ukraine and the Socialist Republic of Vietnam have so far 
signed an agreement on a Ukrainian-Vietnamese intergovernmental 
commission for trade, economic, scientific, and technical 
cooperation, a protocol on trade and economic cooperation in 
1994, an agreement on visa-free entry of diplomatic and service 
passport holders, and an agreement on air transport. 
  The two countries have a long history of bilateral 
relations. 
Ukraine was involved in the development of Vietnam's chemical, 
petrochemical, and food industries, as well as machine-building. 
  During the visit, Vo Van Kiet will meet President of Ukraine 
Leonid Kravchuk, Acting Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy, and 
officials at the Vietnamese Embassy in Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

