<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Denies Possibility of Armed Clash With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Denies Possibility of Armed Clash With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806161394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1500 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0806161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Relations between Ukraine and Russia should be build 
on a long-term basis. The head of our state, Leonid Kravchuk, 
declared this in an interview for the Moscow-based newspaper 
TRUD. According to him, relations between the two countries 
should be sincere and those of partnership, truly friendly and 
equal. Leonid Kravchuk flatly denied a possibility of any 
military clash between Ukraine and Russia. He devoted a 
significant part of his interview to the Crimean issue. It was 
again emphasized that he comes out against any force methods of 
solving it. 

</TEXT>

