<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army To Be Equipped With High-Precision Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army To Be Equipped With High-Precision Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906121794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1039 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk stated that 
following the withdrawal of nuclear weapons, the Ukrainian army 
will be equipped with high-precision weapons, which are not 
weapons of mass destruction. 
  He told the cadets of the Zhitomir military school that 
Ukraine, Russia, the U.S. and other countries were working on 
this type of weapon. 
  The acquisition of high-precision weapons is provided for in 
the Ukrainian military doctrine, approved by the Ukrainian 
parliament in November 1993. 

</TEXT>

