<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kuchma Rejects Political Union With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kuchma Rejects Political Union With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806162594 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1520 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ternopol [no dateline as received] -- Meeting the 
local electorate on 7 June, Leonid Kuchma, presidential 
candidate and leader of the Ukrainian Union of Industrialists 
and Entrepreneurs, was accused of looking to "the Northern 
neighbor" and trying to "pull Ukraine back into Moscow's 
bondage." The candidate replied: "I have never, not even in my 
sleep, ever said anywhere to anyone anything about a political 
union with Russia. As for economic ties, ask people on the shop 
floor, would they reject that?" 
  Meanwhile, Kuchma said he opposed Ukraine's accession to the 
ruble zone: "This would lead to loss of sovereignty." He spoke 
in favor of strong authority which world practice had proven to 
be the only force capable of implementing economic reforms. 
"Only one person should take the responsibility," he added. 
"That's why if I win I will initially act as prime minister as 
well as perform full presidential duties." 

</TEXT>

