<H3> <TI>   Confirms Candidacy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Confirms Candidacy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806180694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1727 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 8 June -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk 
confirmed on Wednesday that he has not changed his mind to run 
for presidency in the presidential elections to be held on 26 
June. 
  "Many good things have been done during my presidency," 
Kravchuk told ITAR-TASS. He admitted, however, that there were 
also mistakes, both subjective and objective. 
  "If I do not embark on the path of building and 
strengthening 
the state and pursuing the course of peace and accord, I would 
not be able to tell the people and myself why I did not do what 
I could," he continued. 
  "That's why the participation in the elections is the 
continuation of my desire to do everything possible so that 
Ukraine could continue to develop," Kravchuk said. 

</TEXT>

