  [Text] A session of the Supreme Soviet Presidium, headed by 
Vyachaslaw Kuznyatsow, first deputy to the Supreme Soviet 
chairman, was held to discuss a range of issues: The 
establishment of diplomatic relations between Belarus and the 
Federal Republic of Yugoslavia; some legislative acts of the 
Republic, regulating the mechanism of mutual accounts in a range 
of national sectors; adoption of a decision to award honorary 
titles and diplomas and Belarusian Supreme Soviet diplomas. A 
report by the Central Election Committee on the implementation 
of measures for holding elections for Belarusian president was 
heard. 

