<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gagauz Leader Assesses Turkish President's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gagauz Leader Assesses Turkish President's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0806173794 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1945 GMT 6 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0806173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Comrat, BASAPRESS, 6/6/1994 -- Turkish President 
Suleyman Demirel's visit to Comrat and Ceadar-Lunga districts is 
of historic importance. He was the first Turkish president to 
visit the region inhabited by Gagauzians, stated to BASA Stepan 
Topal, president of the self-proclaimed Gagauz Republic. 
According to him, "this visit will strongly foster Gagauzians' 
national rebirth in many areas as well as the parliamentary 
settlement of the problem regarding Gagauzians' 
self-determination." The credit worth $32 million, which Turkey 
granted Moldova to develop the Southern districts will 
accelerate the social-economic development of these districts, 
said Topal. 

</TEXT>

