<DOCNO> FBIS4-39670 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov111_b_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-111 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Replacement Rumored for `Health Reasons' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Replacement Rumored for `Health Reasons' </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Kostikov Denies Resignation Allegations </H4>

<F P=102> LD0906101094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1003 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906101094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 9 ITAR-TASS -- "Allegations about Viktor 
Chernomyrdin's resignation are an invention and a lie from 
beginning to end," the Russian president's press secretary 
Vyacheslav Kostikov announced today. 
  The press secretary reacted to a report in the KOMSOMOLSKAYA 
PRAVDA daily, which cited "informed sources in the country's 
leadership" as saying that "the question about Viktor 
Chernomyrdin's resignation from the post of prime minister for 
reasons of health has been decided in principle, as has the 
appointment of Yuriy Skokov to the post". 
  The report said "Viktor Chernomyrdin has reportedly agreed 
with the formula, which accounts for his unexpected departure 
for Germany for medical examination and treatment for 
nephrolithiasis". 
  The newspaper cited unofficial data about the president's 
meeting with Yuriy Skokov last Monday, "as a result of which, 
the relevant draft presidential decrees are awaiting Boris 
Yeltsin's signature". 
  Yuriy Skokov is the chairman of the federation of commodity 
producers and entrepreneurs of Russia. Earlier, he was 
secretary of the Security Council and since October 1992 was 
closely involved with the affairs of the regions, where he won 
considerable popularity, KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA reported. 

</TEXT>

