<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov, Nikita </F>
Yermakov, and Igor Shchegolev] 
  [Text] Paris June 9 TASS -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev left here for Istanbul on Thursday to attend a North 
Atlantic Cooperation Council session. 
  Within the framework of the session of the Council of the 
Organisation for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD), 
Kozyrev signed a package of documents establishing official 
contacts between Russia and the OECD and met with OECD leaders 
and chief delegates of a number of countries. 
  The documents signed open the way for broader effective 
long-term cooperation between Russia and the OECD, cooperation 
which meets the interests of the two sides, Kozyrev pointed out, 
summing up the results of his stay in Paris. 
  "This has become yet another illustration of the 
international community's support for Russian reforms and yet 
another step towards our country's integration into the world 
economy," he said. 

</TEXT>

