<H3> <TI>   France's Juppe Supports Partnership With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    France's Juppe Supports Partnership With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906171294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1616 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul June 9 TASS -- Speaking at a foreign 
minister level sessopn of the NATO Council here today, French 
Foreign Minister Alain Juppe said that he is for an 
all-embracing partnership with Russia in political, economic and 
military spheres. 
  The head of the French Foreign Ministry expounded this stand 
at a closed-door meeting, the AFP news agency reported, quoting 
informed sources. According to Juppe, Western countries must 
not only involve Russia in resolving questions of security in 
Europe, but also propose to Russia to conclude a treaty on 
partnership with the European Unon, induct her into the Council 
of Europe and give her an opportunity to participate in work of 
the G-7's political sphere, the next regular session of which is 
scheduled to be held in Naples in July. 

</TEXT>

