<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Diplomat Seeks Another Meeting on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Diplomat Seeks Another Meeting on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906150294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1355 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906150294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia wants the next "ministerial" meeting on 
settlement in Bosnia and Herzegovina to be held in a week or 
two, a high-ranking Russian diplomat said in an interview with 
INTERFAX on Thursday. 
  He said that the exact time-frame for this meeting could be 
defined before the end of the week. The foreign ministers and 
secretaries of Russia, the U.S.A., Great Britain, France and the 
EU troika (Germany, Greece and Belgium) will discuss these 
issues in Istanbul where they will take part in the meeting of 
the North Atlantic Cooperation Council (NACC). 
  Russia seeks to invite representatives of the parties to the 
conflict in Bosnia to the "ministerial" meeting, to tell them 
about the results of the work of the contact group on the map of 
the demarcation in Bosnia and Herzegovina. After this the 
parties must have two or three weeks to think everything over 
and to settle the disputed issues. Thereafter, a long-term 
agreement putting an end to hostilities must be signed, the same 
sources told INTERFAX. 

</TEXT>

