<H3> <TI>   Moscow To Secure Repayment Deferment From Paris Club </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow To Secure Repayment Deferment From Paris Club </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0806143694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1329 GMT 8 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0806143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia intends to secure from the Paris Club a 
deferment for the repayment of 20 billion dollars, a 
high-ranking representative of the Finance Ministry told the 
Financial Information Agency, commenting on the recent agreement 
on the deferment of the repayment of 7 billion dollars. 
  By agreement with the Paris Club, Moscow will repay the 7 
billion dollars over a period stretching till the year 2010. To 
quote this representative, the talks held in Paris on June 2 and 
3 were based on the March agreement between Moscow and the 
International Monetary Fund on the extension of the second part 
of the 1.5 billion dollar systematic transformation credit. 
  To reach an agreement on deferment, Russia is to secure the 
International Monetary Fund's approval and receive reserve 
credit from it of about 4 billion dollars. 
  Talks between the Central Bank and Finance Ministry on the 
one hand, and the International Monetary Fund on the other are 
to begin next autumn. 

</TEXT>

