<H3> <TI>   Government To Increase Aid to Rwandan Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Increase Aid to Rwandan Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906164894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1604 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 9 TASS -- Russia fully shares the 
intenational community's deep concern over continued violence in 
Rwanda which is aggravating humanitarian crisis in that country, 
Grigoriy Karasin, head of the Information and Press Department 
in the Russian Foreign Ministry, said at a briefing today. 
  The Russian side is taking direct part in operations to 
provide humanitarian aid to Rwandan refugees in Tanzania, where 
a truck detachemnt from Russia is already working. The Russian 
trucks are transporting essential goods to refugee camps. 
Russia intends to increase its participation in this operation, 
and in the near future, in agreement with the U.N., intends to 
send additional 20 trucks and a group of specialists together 
with different kinds of equipment for this purpose, Grigoriy 
Karasin said. 

</TEXT>

