<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Air Space Violated 109 Times in Past Year </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Air Space Violated 109 Times in Past Year </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906202294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1412 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 9 Jun -- The rules of using Russia's air 
space have been violated 109 times in the past year. This was 
done 22 times by aircraft of the former USSR states, and 27 
times by planes belonging to other foreign states. The air 
defense troops have been forced to take decisive measures with 
regard to transgressors. Forty five aircraft were forced to land 
en route or to return to their place of departure. 
  These figures were cited in an appeal by the command of the 
air defense troops to all ministries and departments, as well as 
to the management of Russian commercial and foreign airlines. 
The document, which ITAR-TASS received today from the press 
service of the air defense forces main command, requests that 
the rules for the use of Russian Federation air space be 
strictly observed, and stresses that only concerted action can 
prevent emergency situations, including those involving human 
losses. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

