<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chief Delegate Urges Deeper Dialogue With OAS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chief Delegate Urges Deeper Dialogue With OAS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906110494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1028 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906110494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Chistov] </F>
  [Text] Brasilia June 9 TASS -- The text of a speech made by 
Georgiy Mamedov, leader of the Russian delegation and deputy 
foreign minister, at the 24th session of the General Assembly of 
the Organisation of American States (OAS) in the Brazilian city 
of Belem, was circulated as an official document on Wednesday. 
  Russia, which was granted the status of permanent observer 
at 
the OAS in 1992, comes out in favour of "in-depth dialogue with 
American states sharing common democratic values and the 
striving for security and peace", the document emphasised. 
  The economic reforms experience gained in Latin American 
countries can be of much benefit to Russia. There are real 
prerequisites for broader trade, economic, scientific and 
technical cooperation between Russia and countries in the 
region. The establishment of contacts in the field of advanced 
technology, in space research and the uses of nuclear energy, in 
particular, can be of great importance, the document pointed out. 
  In his speech Mamedov also stressed the importance of 
cooperative action in combating drug trafficking. 
  The OAS, which brings together the United States, Canada, 
and 
32 Latin American countries, was founded in 1948 and is the most 
widely-representative and authoritative hemispheric organisation. 

</TEXT>

