<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Visa-Free Travel Agreement Signed With Slovakia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visa-Free Travel Agreement Signed With Slovakia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0906113394 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 9 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0906113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Travel to Slovakia Possible without </F>
Visa"] 
  [Text] Slovakia is the first of the "Visegrad group" of 
countries to agree to visa-free travel for its citizens and 
citizens of Russia in both directions. An intergovernmental 
agreement was signed here today which introduces liberal 
conditions for travel under a general civil passport. This 
applies to all people who travel to Russia or Slovakia with an 
invitation for private or official business and for tourism or 
medical treatment for a period of up to 30 days. Visas will 
only be needed by those people who intend to look for work or 
change their permanent place of residence. 
  "The agreement which has been signed," Foreign Minister 
Eduard Kukan stated in an interview with your ITAR-TASS 
correspondent, "will help to deepen mutual contacts and 
cooperation between the two countries' citizens. This is 
dictated by the mutual interests of Slovakia and Russia but is 
not evidence of a new emphasis in Slovakia's eastern policy." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

