<H3> <TI>   Karasin on Right To Protect Servicemen in Tajikistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karasin on Right To Protect Servicemen in Tajikistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906163794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1502 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature: Igor Porshnev, </F>
Vitaly Trubetskoi and others] 
  [Text] Moscow reserves the right to use every tool at its 
disposal to protect its servicemen and other Russians in 
Tajikistan. Grigory Karasin, Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman, 
said at a Moscow briefing Thursday that armed terror had been 
and would be dealt with resolutely. 
  He said that the recent killings of Russian servicemen and 
ethnic Russians in Tajikistan was the work of those who did not 
want peace and stability in that country. 
  Karasin also said that at its emergency meeting the Tajik 
government had decided to take up numerous steps to protect the 
Russians and the residents of the Tajik capital. Round the 
clock patrolling had been introduced in areas inhabited by 
Russians. Investigation teams in which military prosecutors are 
represented have been set up. 

</TEXT>

