<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [POSTFACTUM report under the "From Our Correspondents and </F>
News Agencies" rubric: "Ukraine Will Repay Gas Debts in 
Apartments"] 
  [Text] Ukraine is obligated to build 145,000 square meters 
of housing in Russia to pay off its debt to the "Gazprom" 
Russian joint-stock company. 
  As the "Gazprom" Russian joint-stock company reported, the 
Ukrainian debt for gas already supplied amounts to $800 million. 
Ukraine is obligated to build housing for citizens working in 
the north in the gas-production industry to pay off this debt. 
Financial repayment of the debt has for the moment been 
postponed. 

