<H3> <TI>   BPF Leader Sees Russia as Enemy of Independence </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    BPF Leader Sees Russia as Enemy of Independence </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906205594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1601 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Excerpts] Minsk, 9 Jun -- "Being an enormous Eurasian 
state with a history and ideology of an empire, Russia has 
always been, is now, and ever will be the enemy of Belorussia's 
[Belarus] independence and of our freedom, whatever disguise it 
may be wearing," maintains Zenon Poznyak, the leader of the 
Belorussian People's Front [BPF], who is competing for the post 
of the first president of the Republic. An interview with him 
appeared today in the newspaper SOVETSKAYA BELORUSSIA. 
  At the same time, the BPF leader is promising that if he 
wins 
the elections scheduled for 23 June, he will adhere to a 
"friendly but firm policy" in relations with Russia, and is by 
no means going to force Russians out of the republic. [passage 
omitted] 
  The other five candidates for the presidential post 
associate 
the future of Belorussia with close and warm relations with 
their "eastern neighbor." 

</TEXT>

