<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kebich Believes Government `Should Bridle Price Formation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kebich Believes Government `Should Bridle Price Formation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1006090294 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1006090294 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prospects for development, privatization, price 
formation, and other issues were discussed at a Republican 
seminar- conference on trade issues. Head of the Belarusian 
Government Vyachaslaw Kebich delivered a report. Speaking about 
prices for goods, the prime minister stated that the government 
failed to stabilize them thus far. The key reason is an 
exterior factor, however, the minor reason is that trade also 
had its own expenditures. Many middlemen -- boosting prices -- 
have emerged. Their numbers can and should be minimized. 
According to the prime minister, the government should bridle 
price formation through the Department for Prices. 
  The head of the government also met yesterday with the 
working collective of the Kirov factory. 

</TEXT>

