<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prices for Main Foodstuffs Decreased by 15 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prices for Main Foodstuffs Decreased by 15 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0906143294 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1000 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0906143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beginning today, the Cabinet of Ministers' 
resolution has decreased prices for certain foodstuffs by 15 
percent. By issuing this resolution, the Cabinet of Ministers 
took control over mark ups and reduced all of them to (?10) 
percent which enables customers to save a small sum of money. 
  For example, the price for sausages, which stood earlier at 
28.700 rubles [R], decreased by R4.500. Beef became cheaper by 
R3,000 and pork -- by R3.500. Beginning today, prices for bread 
and flour products, meat offals, and butter --which were sold at 
market prices -- have also been changed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

