<H3> <TI>   Bank Releases Report Regarding Indexation of Deposits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bank Releases Report Regarding Indexation of Deposits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1006090594 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 
GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1006090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Savings Bank of Belarus issued a report for 
Supreme Soviet consideration concerning [word indistinct] the 
indexation of individual deposits. This document is a reply to 
Prime Minister Vyachaslaw Kebich's statement regarding the 
necessity to issue 100 percent compensations for people's 
depository losses prompted by inflation. 
  According to experts' estimates, over 1 trillion rubles is 
required to cover the losses -- caused by the devaluation of 
individual deposits -- by 100 percent. It goes without saying 
that it is necessary to repay the population what it lost not 
through its own will, believes Alyaksandr Barkun, deputy 
chairman of the Savings Bank of Belarus. However, two issues -- 
by exactly what sum the deposits will be increased and who will 
pay -- remain unresolved. 

</TEXT>

