<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Border Guards Recoup Half Costs in Seized Contraband </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Border Guards Recoup Half Costs in Seized Contraband </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0906131594 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 8 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM0906131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Colonel Valeriy Kovalev report under "News From the Regions </F>
From Our Correspondents" rubric: "`Green Caps' Become 
`Self-Financing'"] 
  [Text] Minsk -- The Belorussian [Belarusian] Border Troops 
Main Directorate has summarized its operational results for the 
first five months of this year. The Border Troops Main 
Directorate informed KRASNAYA ZVEZDA's correspondent that during 
this period 948 violators had been detained, contraband goods 
worth 11.5 million rubles had been detected, the export of over 
225 tonnes of nonferrous metals had been prevented, and 276 
weapons and 81 kg of drugs had been seized. The border guards 
have returned $750,000 to the state treasury. This sum, 
converted into Belarusian rubles, equals half of the resources 
allocated to the border guard department from the state budget 
for the current year. So the republic's "green caps" are 
earning their keep. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

