<H3> <TI>   Grachev To Fly to Tbilisi, Meet Shevardnadze </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev To Fly to Tbilisi, Meet Shevardnadze </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006075194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0713 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006075194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan 10 June TASS -- Russian Defence Minister 
Pavel Grachev flies to Tbilisi this morning, where he will have 
a meeting with Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze. Later in 
the day, he plans to go to Gudauta, Abkhazia, where the Russian 
345th airborne regiment is stationed. 
  Turning to a dispatch of Russian peace keepers to Abkhazia, 
Grachev, now on a working tour of Transcaucasia, said in Yerevan 
that the military part of the problem on sending a Russian 
peace-keeping force to Abkhazia has been fully resolved. 
  The Russian Defence Ministry prepared for this purpose three 
motorised battalions out of two peace-keeping divisions deployed 
in the Leningrad and Volga Military Districts. They will be 
ready for air-lifting within three days, the minister said. 
  The 345th airborne regiment stationed in Gudauta is also 
ready for the peace-keeping mission. 
  Besides, the minister gave orders to the commander of the 
Russian Army group in Transcaucasia to prepare another three 
battalions for peace-keeping functions. 
  According to Grachev, the question of the dispatch of troops 
to Abkhazia can be resolved only at the political level. Troops 
are ready to fulfill the peace-keeping operation. 

</TEXT>

