<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oil Contracts Signed With Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oil Contracts Signed With Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1399A Baku BAKINETS in Russian No 5, 9-19 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1399A </F>
<F P=104>  Baku BAKINETS </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Iran-Azerbaijan: New Contracts"] </F>
  [Text] Negotiations conducted in Tehran among 
representatives of oil companies of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
and Azerbaijan Republic ended with the signing of two contracts. 
According to them, Azerbaijan oil producers must perform 
engineering-research and seismographic-exploratory work in the 
southeastern part of the Caspian Sea valued at a total of more 
than $3 million. 
  As Azerbaijan State Petroleum Company Vice President 
Khoshbakht Yusuf-zade, Doctor of Geological-Mineralogical 
Sciences, announced, business relations with the National 
Petroleum Company of the neighboring state began to develop at 
the end of the 1960's when Azerbaijani geophysicists did 
research needed by the Iranians for studying the geological 
structure of minerals in the southern part of the Caspian Sea. 
  The Azerbaijani special ships Zokhrab Veliyev and Rezonans, 
which are equipped with everything necessary for performing the 
entire complex of work under the new contracts between the oil 
companies of the two neighboring Caspian states, will soon 
depart for the southern shores of the Caspian Sea. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

