  [Text] President Boris Yeltsin has signed an edict on 
measures to implement the treaty on public accord. A 
conciliation commission [soglasitelnaya komissiya] is being set 
up to deal with this. Sergey Filatov, the head of the 
president's administration, has been appointed its chairman. 
The conciliation commission will cooperate in its work with the 
Federal Assembly's Federation Council and State Duma, as well as 
with parties, social and public movements, and other 
organizations whose representatives signed the treaty on public 
accord. 

