<H3> <TI>   Filatov Reportedly Campaigning for Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov Reportedly Campaigning for Yeltsin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1006074094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 10 Jun 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1006074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["NG" report under the "In Brief" rubric: "Filatov Active"] </F>
  [Text] NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA has come to learn that 
presidential chief of staff Sergey Filatov, who remains in his 
position only thanks to the hue and cry raised around his 
possible resignation, has lately decided to prove his usefulness 
to Yeltsin. According to his plan, the administration's 
structure should have a subdivision (some 120 people in number) 
that would already now launch a campaign for a new president of 
Russia -- Boris Yeltsin. According to NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA's 
information, many "democratically" oriented former people's 
deputies of the Russian Federation have received an invitation 
to join such a service. Some of them have refused, in 
unprintable form. 

</TEXT>

