<H3> <TI>   70 Million Bank Depositors May Get Compensation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    70 Million Bank Depositors May Get Compensation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1006080094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 10 Jun 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK1006080094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [RIA report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- An initiative group has been created in 
the State Duma to formulate a law on compensation of Savings 
Bank deposits made by the population before the freeing of 
prices in January 1992. Grigoriy Bondarev, a "Yabloko" faction 
deputy and one of those who first formed the idea for the future 
law, has said the possibility of compensation in stocks, 
enterprises, apartments, and even service facilities up for 
privatization, rather than in money, is being considered. 
Well-known jurists from the Moscow Private Law Center have been 
asked to draft the law. Bondarev said, however, that the 70 
million affected depositors "should not celebrate victory yet." 
According to him, the idea for such compensation is being 
worked on at the State Committee for the Management of State 
Property but "with no special enthusiasm." 

</TEXT>

