<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chubays Says Privatization Complete </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chubays Says Privatization Complete </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906202594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1936 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 9 (TASS) -- "Privatisation in Russia 
has been carried through," said chairman of the Russian 
committee for state property, Anatoliy Chubays, an interview to 
the "Publicist" studio broadcast by the First Television Channel 
on Thursday. 
  According to Chubays, "the privatisation has been carried 
out 
despite numerous experts' forecasts and stormy political 
developments around it." 
  At the same time, Chubays believes that as far as the state 
property committee is concerned, and for him personally, the 
goal of privatisation goes far beyond the framework of 
privatisation itself. He described privatisation as a very deep 
process "which modifies processes taking place in an economic 
organism at a molecular level." 
  According to Chubays, a total of 70 percent of Russian 
enterprises will be auctioned for vouchers, 20 percent for money 
and 10 percent will not be subject to privatisation at all. 
According to Chubays, enterprises excluded from monetary and 
voucher privatisation include those connected with the 
production of nuclear splitting materials, cipher equipment and 
special kinds of armaments. 

</TEXT>

