<H3> <TI>   Comment on Duma Vote on Defense Expenditures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comment on Duma Vote on Defense Expenditures </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Grachev Disappointed With Military Budget </H4>

<F P=102> LD0906161894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1531 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Yerevan, 9 Jun -- Russian Defense Minister Pavel 
Grachev, in the Caucasus region on a working visit, has 
described the vote held on [the budget] on Wednesday by the 
Russian State Duma as sad. 
  This budget, in his words, can only guarantee the payment of 
the wages and salaries of military servicemen and civilians 
employed by the military establishment. He expressed hope that 
the Army would get some extrabudgetary funding. If we do not 
get additional extra budgetary funds, then there can be no talk 
of ordering new equipment or arms, Pavel Grachev said. 
  He also said that problems would arise with the funding of 
scientific research and design work. This budget will have a 
negative effect on the future of Russia's armed forces, Pavel 
Grachev said. 

</TEXT>

