<H4>    Spokesman: Defense Budget To Be Revised </H4>

<F P=102> LD0906141594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1350 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 9 Jun -- Russia's military budget is to be 
revised, Major General Vladimir Osadchiy, a high-ranking 
spokesman of the Russian Defense Ministry, told Itar-Tass today. 
  According to him, the 40.6 trillion rubles allocated for 
military spending by the State Duma represents a threat to the 
national security of the armed forces. "The defense budget will 
not find support in the upper chamber of parliament, and 
discussion of this pressing problem will be continued," Major 
General Vladimir Osadchiy noted. In so doing, he cited public 
remarks made on this issue by Vladimir Shumeyko and the 
statement by Petr Shurshov, chairman of the Federation Council 
security and defense committee, who said the upper chamber would 
not approve a military budget of less than 55 trillion rubles. 

</TEXT>

