<H3> <TI>   Comment on Duma Vote on Defense Expenditures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comment on Duma Vote on Defense Expenditures </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Mass Rallies Organized Against Cutbacks </H4>

<F P=102> LD0906190194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1741 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mass rallies organized by the association of 
defense workers' unions were held in a number of Russia's cities 
in protest at the destruction of the defense industry. 
  The chairman of the association's central committee, Sergey 
Shuklin, told Interfax that only representatives of the aviation 
industry had failed to take part in the rallies. 
  Shuklin said a number of St. Petersburg enterprises kept 
their sirens on and held shop-floor meetings. Their workers 
also picketed the administrative building. Similar actions were 
also held in Novosibirsk, Barnaul, Kirov, Perm and Moscow. 
  In particular, defense workers demanded their salaries be 
paid, jobs preserved, a mechanism to reconcile mutual debts be 
set up and state control over fuel prices established. 

</TEXT>

