<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Submit 17 Bills on Social Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Submit 17 Bills on Social Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006105094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0919 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 10 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin will submit 17 most important bills to the State Duma 
(lower chamber of the Russian Parliament) in June. They are 
intended to help implement the social concord agreement. Their 
list was today handed out to Duma members. 
  The package includes bills "On the Government of the Russian 
Federation", "On Combatting Organised Crime", "The Criminal Code 
of the Russian Federation", "On General Principles of State 
Power in the Russian Federation", "On Federal Executive Bodies", 
and also on the flag and coat-of-arms of the Russian Federation. 
  The bill on the "Criminal-Procedural Code of the Russian 
Federation" will be the last to be submitted to the State Duma 
-- on June 30. The first ones to be discussed will be two 
bills: "On the Procedure for Adopting and Putting Into Force the 
Federal Constitutional Laws and Federal Laws" and "On Amendments 
to the Law on the State Border". The documents also include a 
bill "On the Right to Information". 
  Yeltsin has instructed his plenipotentiary representative in 
the Federal Assembly to agree with the State Duma and the 
government on their joint work to finalise the bills, which the 
lower chamber of the parliament is to discuss. He also 
instructed the head of the presidential administration to 
appoint the people who will be personally responsible for 
drawing up the bills in conformity with the fixed plan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

