<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Baburin Resigns From Concord For Russia Bloc </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baburin Resigns From Concord For Russia Bloc </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906154094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1355 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sergey Baburin, MP, a leader of the Russian 
All-People's League, officially left the opposition movement 
Concord for Russia. 
  Vasiliy Lipitskiy, chairman of the Social-Democratic Popular 
Party of Russia, told journalists that Baburin had made his move 
following the State Duma's vote Wednesday on the 1994 budget. 
Communist Party and Agrarian Party leaders Gennadiy Zyuganov and 
Mikhail Lapshin voted for the budget draft while Baburin 
rejected it. 
  Baburin jointly with former Russian vice-president Aleksandr 
Rutskoy, Zyuganov, Lapshin, Constitutional Court Justice Valeriy 
Zorkin and the Duma's Economic Policy Committee Chairman Sergey 
Glazyev founded the Concord for Russia opposition movement and 
attended last May's session of the movement's National Council. 
  A week later he said in Novosibirsk, however, that the 
Russian All-People's League would not support Rutskoy, who could 
become the opposition candidate in the coming presidential 
elections. 

</TEXT>

