<H3> <TI>   Communists Call for Abolition of Presidency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Communists Call for Abolition of Presidency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006094694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0831 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 10 TASS -- The communist faction in the 
Russian Parliament's lower house has called for the abolition of 
presidency in Russia and the formation of a government of 
popular trust. 
  The Communist Party of the Russian Federation and its 
faction 
in parliament circulated an official document in the State Duma 
entitled "on the three-year policy of destruction of the basis 
of people's life in Russia" which calls on all "truly patriotic 
and democratic forces to join the lawful struggle for radical 
changes in the policy of the Russian state and the withdrawal of 
the ruling regime from the political arena." 

</TEXT>

