<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 10 TASS -- Artur Chilingarov, a noted 
polar explorer, was elected to become the fifth deputy speaker 
of the Russian State Duma on Friday. 
  247 lawmakers voted for him, 19 against and 28 abstained. 
  An ethnic Armenian, Chilingarov is a member of the "New 
Regional Policy" faction, the president of the Association of 
Polar Researchers and a member of the all-Russian "Renewal" 
union. 
  In Duma he represents the Nenets Autonomous Region. 

</TEXT>

