<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Backs Newspapers' Call for Ownership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Backs Newspapers' Call for Ownership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM0906113194 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 9 Jun 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM0906113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Vasiliy Ustyuzhanin report: "Where Is Our Share?"] </F>
  [text] The State Duma yesterday supported an appeal from 
chief editors of papers and magazines published by the "Pressa" 
publishing house. What do journalists of KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA, 
SELSKAYA ZHIZN, OGONEK, KRESTYANKA, PRAVDA, ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA 
-- around 20 publications in all -- want? In short -- justice. 
  The publishing house had been expanding for many years, 
including on the money of newspapers and magazines. Through 
collective efforts a unique publishing complex was created. But 
following the well-known August events the publishing house 
received state-owned status, while the newspapers got the status 
of juridical entities and...no shares in the property. As a 
result, every editorial collective was forced to conclude a 
lease contract separately with the publishing house on -- let us 
be blunt -- disadvantageous terms. 
  State Duma deputies deemed the demands of the journalists' 
collectives to be well-founded, and proposed that the government 
adopt the necessary measures. 

</TEXT>

