<F P=102>   LD0906164994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1502 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906164994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by INTERFAX Diplomatic Panorama correspondents Igor </F>
Porshnev, Vitaly Trubetskoi and others] 
  [Text] The problem of division of the Black Sea Fleet 
warships and launches, which is discussed by the Russian and 
Ukrainian delegations in Kiev, has been nearly solved. The 
statement was made Thursday [9 June] before the beginning of the 
next round of talks by commander of the Ukrainian Navy, Vladimir 
Bezkorovainy. 
  Speaking about the problem of basing, Bezkorovainy said that 
the Ukrainian Navy could also use the bases leased to the 
Russian Navy. 
  The head of the Russian delegation at the talks, Yuri 
Dubinin 
marked the constructive and friendly situation at the talks. 
  He said that according to the understanding Ukraine should 
have 18.3 pct of Black Sea Fleet's warships. 
  Dubinin said if the sides fail to achieve a definite result 
on Thursday, we shall invite the Ukrainian delegation to Moscow 
to continue talks. 
  Russian Ambassador in Kiev Leonid Smolyakov told 
INTERFAX-Ukraine that still unresolved are the conditions and 
deployment period of the Russian Navy in the Ukrainian territory. 

</TEXT>

