<H3> <TI>   Israel To Sign Cooperation Document 16-17 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israel To Sign Cooperation Document 16-17 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906190094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1530 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, [no dateline as received] -- The embassy of 
the State of Israel in Ukraine has informed UNIAN that it is 
planned that a document, drawn up in Kiev between 6 and 8 June 
by an Israeli delegation, led by the Uri Barner, deputy director 
general for cultural and scientific relations of that country's 
external political department, will be signed during Israeli 
Foreign Affairs Minister Shimon Peres's official visit to 
Ukraine on 16-17 June. This is a cooperation program between 
Israel and Ukraine in the culture and education sphere, aimed at 
implementing the agreement on cooperation in the above field, 
signed in Jerusalem on 12 January 1993. The program plans 
specific cooperation in education and culture (cinema, theater, 
music, fine art, literature, museums, archives), science, 
sports, TV, and radio, as well as exchanges of students, youth 
delegations, and specialists. 

</TEXT>

