  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk submitted to 
parliament his proposals on measures to be taken if the Crimean 
parliament fails to bring its legislation in line with the 
Ukrainian Constitution, head of the presidential press office , 
Nikolai Mikhalchenko, told INTERFAX-Ukraine. However, he 
declined to indicate what measures were proposed by the 
