<H3> <TI>   Crimean Rossiya Bloc Splits Over Talks With Kiev Deputies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Rossiya Bloc Splits Over Talks With Kiev Deputies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1006085994 Lvov POST-INFORM in Ukrainian 1100 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1006085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Lvov POST-INFORM </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 7 June in Simferopol, the Crimean Supreme 
Council held its regular plenary session, at which it discussed 
a document produced by a working group of Ukrainian and Crimean 
deputies. 
  The session definitively confirmed the division of the 
"Rossiya" bloc into the "Rossiya" (around 40 people) and 
"Respublika" (10 people) factions. The former approved the 
document, in which "Respublika" members termed its position as 
"treacherous." 
  It was decided to consider the document and to submit it to 
the Crimean Supreme Council Presidium for discussion. 

</TEXT>

