<H3> <TI>   Public Bodies Urge Candidates To Annul Viskuli Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Public Bodies Urge Candidates To Annul Viskuli Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS0906130494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1000 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS0906130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A RID reporter has learned that the Republican and 
Minsk City Councils [as heard] and the Movement for Democracy, 
Social Progress, and Justice have issued appeals to presidential 
candidates Dubko, Kebich, Lukashenka, and Novikaw. 
  The statements, in particular, urge the candidates to annul 
the Viskuli agreements [leading to the dissolution of USSR], to 
halt the (?capitalist) path of development of the Republic, to 
strengthen and develop the soviets as organs of genuine power of 
the people, to abolish the presidency, to terminate the 
privatization of the all-people ownership, to liquidate the 
existing state symbols by 3 July 1994, to recognize the equal 
rights of the Belarusian and Russian languages, and to restore 
the holiday on 7 November [the day when the socialist revolution 
was held] in their election programs. 

</TEXT>

