<F P=102>   LD0906140694 Tehran IRNA in English 1343 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 9 June, IRNA -- Turkmen President Saparmurat 
Niyazov on Thursday [9 June] expressed satisfaction with 
Tehran-Ashkhabad relations and underscored the "importance" of 
cooperation between the two neighbors in the Caspian Sea. 
  Niyazov made the remarks in a meeting with the visiting 
Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Morteza Sarmadi in Ashkhabad. 
  Sarmadi said relations between Iran and Turkmenistan were a 
model among other regional states and emphasized that bilateral 
relations could not only benefit both nations but could also 
play an "effective" role in maintaining security and stability 
in Central Asia. 
  The two sides also exchanged views on ways of implementing 
agreements previously reached between Iranian and Turkmen 
presidents in the holy city of Mashhad, outcome of Niyazov's 
recent visit to Indonesia and Malaysia, map of Sarakhs-Tajan 
railway which links Central Asia to east Asia and the latest 
developments in the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS). 

</TEXT>

