<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Velichko] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 10 Jun -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin returned to Moscow today from Germany. Let us 
recall that since 5 June he had been undergoing a medical 
examination and a course of treatment there. 
  Regarding the rumors that had appeared about his possible 
resignation from the post of Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin 
stated: "In society there are still forces putting forth 
similar rumors." "They are trying thereby to keep the whole 
country in a state of tension," he emphasized. 
  The prime minister will spend the remainder of his holiday 
until 15 June in Moscow. 

</TEXT>

