<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Soskovets Calls Rumors `Gargage' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Soskovets Calls Rumors `Gargage' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906150094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1330 
GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0906150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 9 Jun -- First Deputy Prime Minister Oleg 
Soskovets has categorically refuted a report that appeared in 
the press about the possible resignation for health reasons of 
Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and the appointment 
of Yuriy Skokov to this post. He called such information 
complete garbage. 
  A well-informed source in the government told the ITAR-TASS 
correspondent today that this evening Chernomyrdin was returning 
from Germany. But the question of his participation in 
tomorrow's all-Russian builders' conference in the Kremlin with 
the participation of the Russian president currently remained 
open. In all probability, Soskovets would deliver a report 
there. 
  Aleksandr Livshits, head of the Russian president's group of 
experts, told the ITAR-TASS correspondent the following 
concerning the fabrications about the possible resignation of 
Chernomyrdin: Such rumors are advantageous only to those who are 
trying to snatch power, and for this purpose to set at 
loggerheads the leaders of the government and the president's 
administration. We are working amid continuous malevolence, but 
our team of reformers will not let this put their nose out of 
joint. 
  At the federation of goods producers, which is chaired by 
Yuriy Skokov, whom the authors of the article in KOMSOMOLSKAYA 
PRAVDA have destined for the post of prime minister, the 
ITAR-TASS correspondent was told: This is mere fiction and 
nothing else, and it is a pity that it compromises our 
federation's leader. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

