<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fraternal Union With Russia, Ukraine Inevitable </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fraternal Union With Russia, Ukraine Inevitable </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0906194394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1846 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0906194394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent Viktor Sakhankov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Minsk, 9 June -- Speaking on Wednesday [8 June] 
evening before representatives of workers' collectives in the 
city of Mogilyov, prime minister of Belarusia Vyacheslav Kebich 
expressed confidence in the inevitability of a durable alliance 
between the three fraternal peoples of Russia, Ukraine and 
Belarusia. He believes this is determined by the historical 
necessity to live together, the economic interests and ancient 
cultural ties. 
  Belarusians cannot and will not be spongers of Russians 
while 
participating in inter-state division of labor and cooperating 
with them on a mutually advantageous basis in all spheres of 
life, the premier noted. 
  The agreement on the unification of the monetary systems of 
the two countries is the first step towards a closer alliance, 
and the head of the Belarusian government is doing everything in 
his power to put into practice these aspirations of the peoples 
of both countries. 
  Touching on national minorities in sovereign Belarusia, 
Vyacheslav Kebich said that for him such a term was 
unacceptable. People of different nationalities live in 
Belarusia and there cannot be any pretext for inter-ethic 
strife, the Belarusian prime minister emphasized. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

