<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko on Assistance for CIS War Veterans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko on Assistance for CIS War Veterans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1006134394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 9 Jun 94 
First Edition p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PM1006134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Care for Veterans"] </F>
  [Text] On the recommendation of Ruslan Aushev, president 
of Ingushetia and chairman of the Council of the CIS Heads of 
Government Committee for Internationalist Troops, the 
Interparliamentary Assembly Council adopted at its session 
yesterday a decree in which the attention of the parliaments of 
the Interparliamentary Assembly's member states is drawn to the 
necessity of providing internationalist troops and their 
families with a full degree of social and legal protection. 
  "The Interparliamentary Assembly Council adopted this 
decision affecting the future of more than 700,000 people with 
practically no discussion," Vladimir Shumeyko said in an 
exclusive interview for an ITAR-TASS correspondent. He 
emphasized that, unfortunately, questions of state social 
assistance and legal protection for veterans of wars and 
military operations in various countries are being resolved with 
difficulty in the CIS, and advocated improving the system to 
implement interstate legal acts on assistance to veterans 
adopted within the framework of the CIS, including the 
monitoring of their execution by the sovereign states' supreme 
legislative organs. Shumeyko expressed the hope that the 
programs for material and everyday and medical provision for war 
veterans agreed by the CIS countries will be backed by budgetary 
finances. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

