<DOCNO> FBIS4-39830 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov113_h_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-113 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tiraspol Accuses Snegur of Stalling Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tiraspol Accuses Snegur of Stalling Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1106205194 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 2000 GMT 9 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1106205194 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tiraspol BASAPRESS, 9/6/1994 -- The press service 
of the president and government of the self-proclaimed Dniester 
Republic made yesterday, 8 June, an official statement 
concerning the negotiations on the granting of a special 
juridical status to the Dniester region. According to the 
statement, Igor Smirnov accuses Moldovan President Mircea Snegur 
of avoiding and slowing the negotiations. The Tiraspol 
authorities also deny any correlation between the solution of 
the Dniester dispute and the solution of the southern districts' 
[ethnic Gagauz'] problems. The press service reports that 
"Smirnov asked Vladlen Vasev, special envoy of the Russian 
president to the negotiations, to put pressure on President 
Snegur in order to force the latter to speed up negotiations." 

</TEXT>

