<H3> <TI>   Nazarbayev Holds Talks With Estonian President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nazarbayev Holds Talks With Estonian President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006175194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1726 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006175194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by KAZTAG-TASS correspondent Ivan Zakharchenko] </F>
  [Text] Almaty 10 June TASS -- President of Kazakhstan 
Nursultan Nazarbayev held talks on Friday [10 Jun] with the 
Estonian delegation headed by President Lennart Meri who came on 
a working visit to Almaty. 
  When discussing various aspects of a foreign policy both 
sides expressed identity or closeness of positions and views in 
all issues. 
  Specifically, the Estonian president said that he liked 
Nursultan Nazarbayev's idea of establishing a Eurasian alliance 
as it is based on democratic principles inherent in the European 
Union which has been functioning successfully for a long time. 
  The talks ended by the signing of a treaty on mutual 
understanding and cooperation between Kazakhstan and Estonia, an 
agreement on cooperation between Ministries of Foreign Affairs 
of both countries. 
  On 12 June the Estonian delegation is due to leave Almaty 
for 
the People's Republic of China. 

</TEXT>

