<H3> <TI>   Government Adopts Resolution on Gold Project </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Adopts Resolution on Gold Project </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106090494 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Russian 2300 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106090494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Kyrgyz Government has adopted a resolution on 
approving a feasibility study report, amendments and changes to 
the general agreement on the Kumtor-Gold project. The 
resolution says that the legalility and the validity of every 
document, which is mentioned by the above resolution complies 
with Kyrgyzstan's legislation both in terms of its conditions, 
provisions and legal powers of those, who have signed each of 
these documents: on behalf of the government of the Republic -- 
the state concern "Kyrgyz-Altyn" [gold], the Kumtor-Gold 
company, the Kumtor-Mounting company, and the Kumtor Operation 
company. 
  In accordance with this resolution, each side is granted all 
powers and [word indistinct] benefits, which are envisaged by 
the legislation of Kyrgyzstan and documents of the Kumtor-Gold 
project. State bodies, organizations, enterprises, and officials 
should take all the nessessary steps so as to implement 
provisions of the document and render comprehensive support and 
assistance in the implementation of the Kumtor-Gold project in 
accordance with the relevant documents. The abovementioned 
resolution, will operate during the time of the Kumtor-Gold 
project's work. 
  Republican ministries, state committees and departments 
should ensure proper control over activities of the joint 
venture Kumtor in accordance with a procedure, which is 
stipulated by Kyrgyzstan's existing legislation. The resolution 
is signed by Kyrgyz Prime Minister Abbas Dzhumagulov. 

</TEXT>

