<H3> <TI>   `Epidemiological State of Emergency' Declared in Bishkek </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Epidemiological State of Emergency' Declared in Bishkek </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106153194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1300 GMT 
11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An "epidemiological state of emergency" has been 
declared in Bishkek, Kirghizia's [Kyrgyzstan] capital. 
According to the Russian News Agency this measure has been 
taken in connection with the fact that there has been a 
considerable increase in the incidence of dysentery and typhoid 
fever in that city. Until further instructions, all markets and 
bazaars in Bishkek are being closed where public health 
requirements are not being complied with. 

</TEXT>

