<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Army in Dushanbe Appeals for Weapons' Surrender </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Army in Dushanbe Appeals for Weapons' Surrender </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006163394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1547 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006163394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 10 June TASS -- As a result of 
round-the-clock joint patrolling of streets in Dushanbe, the 
capital of Tajikistan, by the Republic's security, the Interior 
and Defence Ministry, as well as deployed there Russian military 
contingent units, over 30 firearms were confisticated, military 
sources in Dushanbe told ITAR-TASS today. 
  As reported earlier, with the aim of stabilizing the 
situation in the Tajik capital, a decision was adopted at a 
session of the Coordination Council of the republic's law 
enforcement bodies on 6 June to take additional measures for 
fighting against crimes. The Russian 201 Army Division has set 
up posts, which are being jointly manned with police bodies. A 
mobile radio station is broadcasting the Russian division 
command's appeal to residents of the city to voluntarily 
surrender illegal arms in their possession. Pamphlets carrying 
text of the appeal are being distributed in the capital. The 
patrols have sweeping powers, including carrying out search of 
all types of vehicles, checking documents in possession of the 
citizens and confiscating illegally kept arms. Areas, where 
Russian servicemen and members of their families live, are being 
kept under special guard. 
  It became known today that an attempt was made to attack the 
car of the 201st Divison commander during the evening checking 
of the posts on 7 June. The attacker was disarmed as a result 
of daring decisive action taken by driver Private Salavat 
Galimov. The would-be assassin, identified as Nazar Khoitov, 
born in 1967, was handed over to police. 

</TEXT>

