<H3> <TI>   India To Grant Loan as Part of Cooperation Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    India To Grant Loan as Part of Cooperation Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106121394 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0701 
GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106121394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by TIA correspondent Konstantin Parshin for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 11 Jun -- Indian Minister of State for 
External Affairs Salman Khurshid announced today that India will 
grant Tajikustan a 10-year loan worth $5 million in accordance 
with a program of mutually advantageous coperation and with a 
whole range of documents that were signed yesterday evening. Of 
this money, 85 percent will go toward implementing joint Tajik- 
Indian projects in the areas of enterprise and industrial 
installation construction, while the remainder will be used for 
acquiring medical equipment. 
  Tajik Foreign Minister Rashid Olimov said at a press 
conference that was devoted to the visit by the Indian minister 
and a delegation of Indian entrepreneurs accompanying him, that 
relations between the two countries were entering a new stage. 
The fact that a plenipotentiary ambassador of India to 
Tajikistan would be appointed in Dushanbe in the near future was 
yet more proof of this. 

</TEXT>

