<F P=100> Turkmenistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Speaker Arrives in Tehran for 3-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Speaker Arrives in Tehran for 3-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106192394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1845 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Oleg Kuzmin] </F>
  [Text] Tehran 11 June TASS -- A Turkmen parliamentary 
delegation led by Parliament Speaker Sakhat Muradov arrived in 
Iran on a three-day visit on Saturday [11 June]. 
  Meeting journalists at Tehran's airport upon his arrival, 
Muradov said that Iran and Turkmenistan have "very good" 
relations and called for their development, including between 
the parliaments of the two countries. 
  Iranian Parliament Chairman 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri welcomed 
Muradov's visit as useful for stepping up the implementation of 
previous bilateral agreements. 
  Muradov and Nateq-Nuri will discuss among other things the 
construction of a gas pipeline from Turkmenistan to Europe via 
Iran. The agreement to this effect was reached earlier and 
confirmed by the Iranian and Turkmen presidents during their 
one-day meeting in the Iranian city of Mehrabad in late May. 

</TEXT>

