<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] On 10 June, Uzbek President Islam Karimov, on 
the occasion of the return of the pilgrims from the holy 
pilgrimage of hajj, received Abdulghani Abdullayev, chairman of 
the Committee for Religious Affairs of the Cabinet of Ministers 
of the Republic and Mufti Mukhtarkhan Abdullayev, head of the 
spiritual board of the Muslims of Transoxania [place name as 
heard]. Karimov congratulated the pilgrims on their successful 
hajj. [passage omitted] 
  There is no point in hiding that there are forces who speak 
badly of our independence. It is from here that we must make 
the people understand the successes of independence. [words 
indistinct] The participants of the meeting expressed their 
gratitude to the president on behalf of all the pilgrims for the 
financial assistance and the special flights made available for 
them. [passage omitted] 
  I can recall very well, said Karimov, that during the 
Communist Party's rule it was difficult for the people even to 
visit the (mosque) and for women to use headscarves when [words 
indistinct]. Thanks to independence all [words indistinct] but 
still unfortunately there are those who do not appreciate these 
opportunities [words indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

