<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tashkent's Gas Stations To Be Privatized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tashkent's Gas Stations To Be Privatized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006112994 Tashkent Radio Tashkent Network in Uzbek 0530 
GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent Radio Tashkent Network </F>
<F P=105>  Uzbek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Uzbek Cabinet of Ministers adopted a decision on 
privatizing gasoline stations in Tashkent city. During 1994 
five working gas stations and four still in the draft stage or 
under construction in Tashkent city will be privatized. The 
Republic's Committee for State Property, the Uzbek petroleum 
products association, and the Tashkent city mayors office 
[Hakimiyat] have been instructed to offer the gas stations for 
sale by auction as private property to physical and legal 
persons including foreigners on the basis of competition. Long 
leases should be issued for the land occupied by the privatized 
gas stations in line with existing legislation. 
  The owners of the privatized gas stations can sell imported 
raw material and petroleum products from outside Uzbekistan at 
their gas stations. 
  The full text of the decree will be published in the press. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

