  [Text] Yerevan ("YERKIR" daily - Haylour), 06/10/94 -- 
Official delegation of the Russian Defense Ministry, headed by 
the Chairman of the Operative Department General-Colonel V. 
Varennikov visited Gyumri on June 9. 
  During a short interview in the airport Varennikov said, the 
goal of the visit is to resolve several organizational problems 
related with stationing of Russian units. 
  General-Colonel noted that on the very first day of the 
visit 
P. Grachev discussed the Russian project on peaceful resolution 
of the Karabakh problem with the President Levon Ter-Petrosyan, 
who positively evaluated the plan. "In fact, L. Ter-Petrosyan 
accepted all our proposals", he stressed. 
  The delegation returned to Yerevan on the same day. 

</TEXT>

