<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Says No Russian Plans for Military Base </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Says No Russian Plans for Military Base </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1106190794 Baku TURAN in English 1835 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1106190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, June 11 (TURAN) -- Today TURAN was told by 
Helen Agapova, Russian Defense Minister's assistant for public 
relations, that Russia does not plan to set up military bases at 
Azerbaijan's territory. According to Agapova, Russia does not 
intend to obtain the status of military base to Gabala 
radio-location station as well. "It is a separate 
radio-technical unit which we want to use ourselves without 
Azerbaijan and free of charge. But we need Azerbaijan's 
agreement for that", she said. 

</TEXT>

