<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze, Yeltsin Discuss Abkhazia Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze, Yeltsin Discuss Abkhazia Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206184994 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in 
Georgian 1700 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1206184994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi First Program Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As reported earlier, Georgian Head of State Eduard 
Shevardnadze and Russian President Boris Yeltsin had a telephone 
conversation yesterday. 
  Mr. Eduard Shevardnadze expressed satisfaction with decrees 
issued by the Russian president recently concerning the 
introduction of peacekeeping forces to Abkhazia. The head of 
state gave a positive assessment of Russian Defense Minister 
Grachev's visit, who came to Georgia on Yeltsin's instructions. 
  For his part, the Russian president expressed satisfaction 
with improved relations between our countries, which have 
already produced positive results in Abkhazia. He also stressed 
the need for a speedy settlement of the conflict and a timely 
return of refugees to Abkhazia. 
  The leaders of the two countries also discussed pressing 
issues relating to peace and stability in the Caucasus. 

