<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Election Nullification Expected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Election Nullification Expected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306095994 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0800 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306095994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A by-election was held in Rustavi yesterday. Last 
night, speaking on Georgian TV, Besik Jalaghania, chairman of 
the Rustavi Electoral Commission, said the elections went 
smoothly and without hindrance until noon. At that time armed 
units appeared in town, who, according to Jalaghania, tried to 
exert pressure on voters and members of the Electoral 
Commission. It became impossible to continue the voting 
procedure in some polling stations. 
  According to Jalaghania members of the Mkhedrioni 
[paramilitary units united under the Georgian Rescue Corps] were 
among those causing the destabilization. The Mkhedrioni press 
center circulated a report that the organization had nothing in 
common with any of the candidates. Therefore, the small units 
acting in Rustavi yesterday did it on their own initiative. 
  Jalaghania also said that because of the disturbances he had 
to quit the elections and get away from Rustavi. He thinks that 
the by-election in Rustavi may be considered void. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

