<H3> <TI>   Meri Arrives in PRC for Cooperation Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meri Arrives in PRC for Cooperation Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306053694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0454 
GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306053694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Spirin] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 13 June -- Estonian President Lennart Meri 
and a delegation of Estonian businessmen have arrived in Beijing 
on an official visit at the invitation of the Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin. ITAR-TASS learned today from well-informed sources 
that at the forthcoming talks with Chinese leaders, L. Meri will 
discuss the prospects for bilateral cooperation, primarily in 
trade and sea transport, and international problems, including 
China's relations with Estonia and the CIS. A meeting of the 
heads of state is also expected today. L. Meri will spend seven 
days in China. 

