<H3> <TI>   Russia, U.S. Agree on Sanctions Against DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia, U.S. Agree on Sanctions Against DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006172994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1608 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006172994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul June 10 TASS -- Russia and the United 
States agreed to submit to the U.N. Security Council's 
consideration the joint resolution on sanctions against North 
Korea linked with the nuclear programme of this country and hold 
an international conference on security and nuclear-free status 
of the Korean penisular, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev 
and U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher told a joint 
press conference in Istanbul on Friday. 
  The resolution will be submitted to the U.N. Security 
Council's consideration "within the next few days", Warren 
Christopher pointed out. 

</TEXT>

