<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Comments on NATO Program, Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Comments on NATO Program, Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006174994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1727 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006174994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Dmitriy Gorokhov and Sergey </F>
Feoktistov] 
  [Text] Istanbul June 10 TASS -- Russia considers the 
Partnership for Peace program to be an area of European 
cooperation, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev said here 
today upon the completion of his meeting with U.S. Secretary of 
State Warren Christopher. 
  Kozyrev said he will soon visit Brussels to give a boost to 
the Partnership for Peace framework document and the program of 
Russian- NATO interaction. He said this program should not 
include mutual vetoes and "surprises". 
  The Russian minister voiced the need for the soonest holding 
of the second conference on Bosnia with participation of 
ministers from Russia, the United States and five nations of the 
European Union but stressed the conference should be well 
prepared. He called on the conflicting sides for political 
settlement of their differences and termination of combat 
operations in Bosnia. 
  In his turn, U.S. Secretary of State Warren Christopher said 
that his negotiations with Andrey Kozyrev discussed cooperation 
in provision of stability and security around the globe. The 
sides exchanged opinions of bilateral relations and called for 
the development of a constructive dialogue to help settlement of 
regional conflicts and differences. 

</TEXT>

