<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Interviewed Prior to Departing Istanbul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Interviewed Prior to Departing Istanbul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006215194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1920 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006215194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by correspondent A. Pishchayev; from the "Vesti" </F>
newscast] 
  [Excerpts] A meeting of the North Atlantic Cooperation 
Council [NACC] at the foreign minister level in Istambul, 
Turkey, summed up the results of NACC's work over the half-year. 
[passage omitted] 
  In a brief interview with Vesti prior to his departure by 
air 
Andrey Kozyrev noted that on the whole we have no fundamental 
differences with NATO. Meanwhile, he said, NATO members do not 
in all ways share the principle of the full equality of NACC 
members, on which we insist. They prefer the formula NATO plus 
partners. In particular this was reflected in the communique on 
the NACC meeting. 
  [Begin recording] [Kozyrev] I could not agree with certain 
formulas, which to my mind take insufficient account of Russia's 
role. For instance, concerning Karabakh, a formula is being 
proposed that notes and stresses only the role of the CSCE. We 
do not demand anything special, but our interests must be taken 
into account. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

