<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Committee Expresses Concern Over U.S. House Resolution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106225294 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 2200 GMT 
11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106225294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The committee for international affairs of the 
Russian State Duma has expressed concern over the adoption by 
the House of Representatives of the U.S. Congress of a 
resolution in favor of the unilateral lifting of embargo on arms 
supplies to Bosnian Muslims. 
  The statement adopted by the lower chamber of the Russian 
parliament notes that such a measure would lead to an escalation 
of conflict in southern Yugoslavia [as heard] and undermine the 
current peace process. In this situation the committee sees it 
as its obligation to reaffirm a recommendation to the president 
and the government of the Russian Federation to study the 
question of taking practical measures to lift unjustified 
sanctions imposed on the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

