<H3> <TI>   Cooperation Discussed With Armenian Parliamentarians </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperation Discussed With Armenian Parliamentarians </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106134394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1314 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 11 TASS -- The speakers of the Russian 
Parliament upper chamber and the Armenian Parliament specified 
some items for their cooperation at their meeting at the upper 
chamber on Saturday. 
  Telling this to journalists, Russian Speaker Vladimir 
Shumeyko noted that a cooperation agreement between the two 
chambers of the Russian Parliament and the Armenian Parliament 
was signed on Friday. 
  The two speakers agreed that it is necessary to establish 
inter- committee parliamentary relations and develop their 
contacts while drafting legislative acts in order to boost ties. 
  Armenian Speaker Babken Ararktsyan stressed: "We highly 
assess relations in the framework of the inter-parliamentary 
assembly and claim at the same time that bilateral parliamentary 
contacts should be also developed". 
  The sides discussed problems connected with Nagorno-Karabakh 
at the meeting. Noting that the Bishkek protocol is still in 
force, Shumeyko stressed that the meetings of parliament 
speakers in St. Petersburg and Moscow "plotted a good road for 
the negotiating process to settle the Armenian-Azeri conflict 
with the participation of the third party -- the 
Nagorno-Karabakh parliament". 
  The Armenian speaker invited Shumeyko to visit his country. 

</TEXT>

