<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Prime Minister Arrives in St. Petersburg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese Prime Minister Arrives in St. Petersburg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006162694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1440 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lev Rumyantsev] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg June 10 TASS -- Vietnamese Prime 
Minister Vo Van Kiet arrived in St. Petersburg on an unofficial 
visit on Friday. 
  On Saturday he will meet with governor of the Leningrad 
region Aleksander belyakov and St. Petersburg Mayor Anatoliy 
Sobchak. 
  During his visit the Vietnamese prime minister will visit 
the 
Hermitage, the St. Peter Fortress and other places. 
  On June 12 Vo Van Kiet will leave for Kazakhstan and on June 
15- 17 arrive in Russia on an official visit to meet with 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and hold talks with Russian 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin to discuss bilateral 
relations and international issues. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

