<H3> <TI>   Visits Mayor's Office </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Visits Mayor's Office </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106201294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1918 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lev Rumyantsev] </F>
  [Text] St. Petersburg June 11 TASS -- Vietnamese Prime 
Minister Vo Van Kiet paid an unexpected visit to St. Petersburg 
on Saturday to wait for the Russian prime minister to return 
from his vacation. 
  Originally, the talks between the 70-member Vietnamese 
delegation and the Russian Government were scheduled for June 8- 
10, but were postponed because of Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin's vacation until June 15-17. 
  The remaining four days the Vietnamese premier decided to 
spend in St. Petersburg, Russia's second largest city and the 
twin city of Ho Chi Minh City. 
  At a meeting at the St. Petersburg mayor's office, Vo Van 
Kiet regretted that there is still some mistrust left in 
relations between Russia and Vietnam, but added that "Russia is 
a special friend" for Vietnam. "The former Soviet Union always 
helped us in the most difficult periods of Vietnam's life. We 
will never forget that," the premier said. 

</TEXT>

