<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cypriot Foreign Minister Views `Successful' Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cypriot Foreign Minister Views `Successful' Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006135594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1305 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1006135594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksey Yerovchenkov] </F>
  [Text] Nicosia June 10 TASS -- "I believe that my visit to 
Russia was successful from every point of view, and the talks I 
had with Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev in Moscow were very 
resultative," Cyprus Foreign Minister Alexandros Mikhailidhis 
told ITAR-TASS at the International Airport of Larnaca upon his 
return home from Russia. 
  "There are sufficient grounds for this success, because 
Russia and Cyprus are linked by good relations from time 
immemorial. We have a common culture and we worship the same 
religion. The peoples of our two countries are cooperating 
fruitfully in the economic sphere". 
  "I wish to note especially my talks with Andrey Kozyrev, 
which were marked by an atmosphere of complete mutual 
understanding," the minister stressed. "The Russian side has 
displayed not only its understanding of the Cyprus problem, but 
also readiness to help resolve it in every possible way. It is 
also pertinent to note that Russia is behind two out of the five 
versions for settling the Cyprus problem, included in the report 
of the U.N. secretary- general. All this gives food for 
satisfaction and we hope that a correct way was found to settle 
the Cyprus problem." 
  "Problems linked with the expansion of Russo-Cyprus economic 
relations were also thoroughly discussed in Moscow. For 
instance, we examined the possibility of implementing an 
inter-governmental agreement, which envisages the participation 
of Cyprus in the development of one of the Black Sea regions of 
Russia, mainly the Krasnodar territory. I have visited that 
region and it produced a very good impression on me. I think 
that our cooperation with the Krasnodar territory will be 
mutually profitable and successful." 
  "To put it in a nutshell," Mikhailidhis noted, "new broad 
vistas for deepening multilateral cooperation are now opening up 
before our two nations." 

</TEXT>

