<H3> <TI>   Two Peacekeepers Killed in Ingushetia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Peacekeepers Killed in Ingushetia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306091894 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two Russian servicemen were killed in Malgobek in 
the Ingush Republic on 12 June. They were members of the 
peacekeeping forces deployed in the state of emergency area. 
  The two were killed at midday in the town's market place, in 
front of witnesses. Vadim Moyseyev, major in the interior 
service, died from two shots in the back. Militia sergeant 
Danie Baydashev sustained seven bullet wounds. 
  The killers escaped from the scene of the crime in a motor 
vehicle. However, their identity has been established through 
the efforts of the investigation group from the Russian Interior 
Ministry and Ingushetia's Interior Ministry and Procuracy. The 
search for the criminals is under way, RIA reports. 

</TEXT>

