<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dagestan Adopts New Constitution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dagestan Adopts New Constitution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106193094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1842 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1106193094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gadzhi Shamov] </F>
  [Text] Makhachkala June 11 TASS -- The parliament of 
Dagestan, a republic in southern Russia, adopted a new 
Constitution at an emergency session on Saturday. 
  The new Constitution provides for a 120-member one-house 
legislature, a State Council -- supreme body of executive power 
-- consisting of 14 people, one from each of 14 ethnic groups 
inhabiting the republic, a government accountable to the State 
Council, and a Constitutional Assembly, half of which will 
consist of parliament deputies and the other half of 
representatives of local councils. 
  The Constitutional Assembly will have the right to elect 
members of the State Council and adopt amendments to the 
Constitution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

