<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Poll: Yeltsin Still Most Popular Politician </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Poll: Yeltsin Still Most Popular Politician </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1106205494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 2000 GMT 
11 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1106205494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Boris Yeltsin is still the most popular Russian 
politician, according to a public opinion poll carried out in 
Moscow in the run-up to independence day, by the Institute of 
Sociology and Parliamentarism. 
  At the same time, the number of people in the capital who 
agree with, or express some positive interest in, the 
president's policies is down from 55 percent in May 1991 to 28 
percent in May this year. The number of Muscovites who do not 
agree with the president's policies has increased from 13 to 23 
percent over this period. 

</TEXT>

