<H3> <TI>   `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Russia's Choice Renamed </H4>

<F P=102> LD1206095194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0853 
GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1206095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 12 Jun -- Delegates of the founding congress 
being held in the Russian Parliamentary center, have unanimously 
voted to approve the name of the new party, which will be called 
Russia's Democratic Choice [Demokraticheskiy Vibor Rossii]. 
  The party has been created on the basis of the Russia's 
Choice movement and faction. But Yegor Gaydar, leader of the 
faction, pointed out that the word "democratic" was added to the 
name for the sake of definition and to indicate what kind of 
choice we are offering Russia. 
  The delegates of the congress have also adopted, as a basis, 
the program and the rules of the new party. 

</TEXT>

