<H3> <TI>   `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Political Council Elected </H4>

<F P=102> LD1306081894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0757 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306081894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 13 TASS -- Yegor Gaydar has been 
elected the chairman of Russia's Democratic Choice Party. The 
results of voting by secret ballot were announced on Monday, the 
second day of the party's founding congress proceedings. 
Gaydar's candidacy was carried by 490 votes to 14. 
  The party's political council was elected as well. On the 
council are, in particular, Anatoliy Chubays, Fedor 
Shelov-Kovedyayev, Bella Denisenko, Boris Zolotukhin, Aleksandrr 
Pochinok, Sergey Yushenkov, Ilya Zaslavskiy and other prominent 
political and public figures. 

</TEXT>

