<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Party Approves Rules, Program </H4>

<F P=102> LD1306161694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1351 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1306161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Any Russian citizen aged 18 and more can join the 
newly formed Russia's Democratic Choice party, if he or she 
shares its fundamental principles, observes its rules and does 
not belong to other political parties. 
  These are the rules of the new party approved by the 
founding 
congress that ended in Moscow on Monday. It also approved as a 
whole the party program that should be finalized by the Council, 
a body that will lead the party between congresses due once in 
two years. 
  In the council each territorial chapter shall be represented 
by one person plus one delegate for each 80,000 voters who cast 
their ballots for Russia's Choice in the parliamentary elections 
in December 1993. The council will consists of a total of 134 
persons, according to the party chairman Yegor Gaydar. 
  Closing the congress he said that many people expect the new 
organization to prevent extremists from coming to power, defend 
the right of citizens to a free and happy life, "a deserving 
future of Russia". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

