<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaydar Interviewed on Democratic Choice Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gaydar Interviewed on Democratic Choice Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1306134694 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1100 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1306134694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Exclusive" interview with Yegor Gaydar, chairman of </F>
Russia's Democratic Choice, by Nikolay Ivanov; place and date 
not given; from the "Novosti" newscast -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Ivanov] You have said that the new party is not a 
party belonging to a certain class, is that not so? In your 
view, whose party is it, in that case? 
  [Gaydar] It is the party for those people who want a calm 
and dignified future for Russia. It is the party for those who 
do not wish their children to fight for a way out to the Indian 
Ocean. It is the party for those who are well aware that there 
is no going back, and that any experiments in that direction are 
dangerous, that we have one proper path -- namely, to be a 
civilized, democratic, market society. 
  The problem with us is that we often do not know how to 
explain and defend these ideas and, as a result, yield the field 
of political struggle to people who have a single, very simple 
little idea, and a very dangerous little idea, namely: let's 
find a non-Russian enemy and try to turn Russian society against 
that enemy. So, in order to prevent such people from gaining the 
political arena we need a serious and effective democratic 
organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

