<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov Wants Russian Democrats To Unite </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov Wants Russian Democrats To Unite </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1206165494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1540 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1206165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sergey Filatov, the Russian president's chief of 
staff, expressed his regret that the democratic forces of the 
country were not united and called for convening a Congress of 
Russia's Democratic Forces. 
  Talking to journalists outside the hall where the founding 
congress of the Russia's Democratic Choice was held, he said 
that such a forum could be convened next fall to overcome the 
disunity. 
  Asked whether he would join Russia's Democratic Choice, 
whose 
congress he had helped to organize, Filatov said that he would 
do so if the platform of that organization suited him. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

