<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Edict on Public Accord Treaty Implementation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict on Public Accord Treaty Implementation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1006210994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0840 
GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1006210994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 10 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin has signed a decree on "Measures for Implementing 
the Treaty on Public Accord [TPA]." The presidential press 
service released the full text of the decree today: 
<H5>  Measures for Implementing the Treaty on Public Accord. </H5>
  To ensure that the articles of the TPA are implemented: 
  1. A Conciliation Commission for Implementing the TPA 
[CCITPA] is to be created in accordance with section 7 of the 
TPA. 
  2. S. A. Filatov, the head of administration of the 
president of the Russian Federation, is to be established as 
chairman of the CCITPA. 
  3. The chairman of the CCITPA is to set up the CCITPA within 
two weeks with the agreement of the Federation Council and the 
State Duma of the Federal Assembly, the government of the 
Russian Federation, and the Public Chamber under the president 
of the Russian Federation. 
  In its work, the CCITPA interacts with the Federation 
Council 
and the State Duma of the Federal Assembly, with the government 
of the Russian Federation, with parties, with social and 
political movements, and with other organizations and 
establishments whose representatives signed the TPA. It also 
coordinates the implementation of the treaty. 
  4. Co-chairmen of the Public Chamber under the president of 
the Russian Federation are to define more precisely the 
composition of the Public Chamber under the president of the 
Russian Federation, to increase the number of its members taking 
into account the signing of the TPA; and to organize the 
analysis and the formulation of recommendations as to the 
implementation of fundamental provisions of the said treaty. 
  5. To set up commissions within the Public Chamber under the 
Russian Federation president: on political stability; on social 
and economic problems; on the federative structure and on 
interethnic relations; on security; and on science, education, 
and culture. They are to analyze the progress of the 
implementation of the TPA and to work out recommendations that 
will be considered at a session of the Public Chamber under the 
president of the Russian Federation and presented to the CCITPA. 
  6. The Public Chamber under the Russian Federation president 
is to ensure the preparation of coordinated proposals on the 
implementation of the TPA. 
  7. The chairman of the CCITPA and co-chairmen of the Public 
Chamber under the Russian Federation president are to brief the 
president on a monthly basis about the progress of the 
implementation of the TPA. 
  8. The department of the president's administration for the 
interaction between parties and public movements and the 
steering department of the administration of the Russian 
Federation president are to ensure the implementation of the TPA 
by the CCITPA. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

